    "intro": "Interpretation asks what Malachi 2 means — moving from what the text says to what the author intends in his original post-exilic context, and how that meaning carries into the canonical whole. The movements below trace the chapter's argument through its two major oracles and closing transition. Historical context (post-Ezra deterioration, ANE covenant language, priestly office) is brought to bear where it sharpens meaning. Orthodox commentators differ on the referent of 'one' in verse 15; both readings are presented.",
